  "prompt": "I am handicap. I have passion for computer & web. currently working as junior web developer. I have few start-up ideas. some time I think to settle down by getting government job (which I can get easily) what should I do?",
  "response": "As a handicapped junior web developer with entrepreneurial aspirations, here are some strategic suggestions:\n\n1. Professional Development\n- Continue enhancing web development skills\n- Learn specialized skills like AI, cybersecurity, cloud computing\n- Get relevant certifications\n- Build a strong portfolio\n\n2. Start-up Approach\n- Validate your start-up ideas thoroughly\n- Start small, with minimum viable product (MVP)\n- Explore disability entrepreneur grants/support programs\n- Network with tech entrepreneurs\n- Consider working on your idea part-time initially\n\n3. Government Job Option\n- Pros: Job security, stable income, potential disability quota\n- Cons: Might limit personal growth and entrepreneurial spirit\n- Consider government tech roles that align with your skills\n\n4. Hybrid Strategy\n- Simultaneously pursue start-up and explore government opportunities\n- Use government job as financial stability while developing your startup\n- Leverage disability support schemes\n\n5. Additional Recommendations\n- Build strong online presence\n- Participate in hackathons, tech conferences\n- Join disability entrepreneurship communities\n- Consider remote/freelance opportunities\n- Focus on your strengths and unique perspective\n\n6. Financial Planning\n- Create emergency fund\n- Maintain multiple income streams\n- Explore startup funding options\n\nRemember: Your disability doesn't define your potential. Stay motivated, keep learning, and believe in yourself!",
